  "text": "Among the several factors affecting the CO 2 emissions, both Zhou et al. [CITATION_1] and Yan et al. [CITATION_2] have proved that economic activity, energy efficiency, and changes in the fuel-mix have the most significant influence in the case of China's thermal electricity sector. Thus, in order to deepen the research of Zhou et al. [CITATION_3] and Yan et al. [CITATION_4] , as well as to proceed with the Shapley/Sun Index for IDA, we consider the following three factors in this study: carbon emission factor (C t F ), energy intensity (C t I ), and economic activity factor (C t G ). Then the CO 2 emissions (C t ) from thermal electricity generation in year t can be decomposed as:",
